Costume Candy Counter
You are provided with a list called costumeList, where each item is a TrickOrTreater record containing three fields: Id, costumeName, and candyCollected.


apex
Copy
public class TrickOrTreater {
    public String Id;
    public String costumeName;
    public Double candyCollected;
}
Your task is to determine which Halloween costume collected the most candy across all trick-or-treaters. Return this costumeName. There will always be exactly 1 costume to return.



Example 1:

Input: costumeList =

apex
Copy
[
  {"Id": "TOT68b00001PxVWiAAN", "costumeName": "Witch", "candyCollected": 100.00}, 
  {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi7AAB", "costumeName": "Witch", "candyCollected": 200.00}, 
  {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi8AAB", "costumeName": "Vampire", "candyCollected": 150.00} 
]
Output: Witch


**Explanation**: The first two trick-or-treaters wore "Witch" costumes, collecting 100 + 200 = 300 pieces of candy. "Vampire" collected only 150 pieces. Since 300 > 150, "Witch" is returned as the ultimate candy-collecting costume! üç¨


Example 2:

Input: costumeList =

apex
Copy
[
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001PxVWiAAN", "costumeName": "Ghost", "candyCollected": 500.50},
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi7AAB", "costumeName": "Superhero", "candyCollected": 620.40},
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi8AAB", "costumeName": "Zombie", "candyCollected": 80.20}
]
Output: Superhero


**Explanation**: Each trick-or-treater wore a different costume. The one who collected the most candy was dressed as "Superhero" with 620.40 pieces, so it is returned as the candy champion! üéÉüç´


Example 3:

Input: costumeList =

apex
Copy
[
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001PxVWiAAN", "costumeName": "Pumpkin", "candyCollected": 300.23},
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi7AAB", "costumeName": "Pumpkin", "candyCollected": 190.20},
   {"Id": "TOT68b00001Tovi8AAB", "costumeName": "Pumpkin", "candyCollected": 20.20}
]
Output: Pumpkin


**Explanation**: All trick-or-treaters wore the beloved "Pumpkin" costume. This festive favorite is returned as it had the highest total candy collected across all trick-or-treaters! üéÉüç≠
/./////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
class Solution {
    public String getTopCandyCostume(List<TrickOrTreater> costumeList){
        Decimal countHigh=0.0;
        Decimal countHigh1=0.0;
        Decimal countHigh2=0.0;
        String winner;
        Map<String,Decimal> CostumeWinnerMap= new Map<String,Decimal>();
        for(TrickOrTreater costume :costumeList ){
           if(CostumeWinnerMap.containsKey(costume.costumeName) == false){
            CostumeWinnerMap.put(costume.costumeName,costume.candyCollected);
           }
           else if(CostumeWinnerMap.containsKey(costume.costumeName) == true){
            countHigh =CostumeWinnerMap.get(costume.costumeName)+costume.candyCollected;
            CostumeWinnerMap.put(costume.costumeName,countHigh);
           }
    }
        for(TrickOrTreater costume :costumeList ){
         countHigh1 =CostumeWinnerMap.get(costume.costumeName);  
        if(countHigh1 > countHigh2){
            countHigh =costume.candyCollected;
            winner = costume.costumeName;
           }
         countHigh2=countHigh1;  
        }
    return winner;
}
}
